  <section id="solutions" class="section solutions-section">
   <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title" id="solutions-title">Existing Solutions</h2>
    <div class="solution-item">
     <div class="solution-header">
      <div class="solution-number">
       1
      </div>
      <div class="solution-title">
       Climate Change Act of 2009 (RA 9729)
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="solution-details">
      <div class="detail-box">
       <div class="detail-label">
        Current Status
       </div>
       <div class="detail-text">
        Climate Change Commission (CCC) is fully operational and leads national climate policy. Climate strategies are integrated into development plans across agriculture, health, and infrastructure sectors.
       </div>
      </div>
      <div class="detail-box">
       <div class="detail-label">
        Procedure/Program
       </div>
       <div class="detail-text">
        Integrates climate strategies into national and local planning. Implementation varies across local government units (LGUs).
       </div>
      </div>
      <div class="detail-box">
       <div class="detail-label">
        Effect/Result
       </div>
       <div class="detail-text">
        Strengthens climate resilience and supports emission reduction goals nationwide.
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
    <div class="solution-item">
     <div class="solution-header">
      <div class="solution-number">
       2
      </div>
      <div class="solution-title">
       National Climate Change Action Plan (NCCAP)
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="solution-details">
      <div class="detail-box">
       <div class="detail-label">
        Current Status
       </div>
       <div class="detail-text">
        Long-term strategy guiding national and local climate actions. CCC regularly evaluates progress and updates the plan based on climate risk assessments and stakeholder consultations.
       </div>
      </div>
      <div class="detail-box">
       <div class="detail-label">
        Procedure/Program
       </div>
       <div class="detail-text">
        Focuses on food security, water sufficiency, ecological stability, and sustainable energy development.
       </div>
      </div>
      <div class="detail-box">
       <div class="detail-label">
        Effect/Result
       </div>
       <div class="detail-text">
        Guides LGUs and agencies in implementing climate-responsive programs and policies.
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
    <div class="solution-item">
     <div class="solution-header">
      <div class="solution-number">
       3
      </div>
      <div class="solution-title">
       Renewable Energy Act of 2008 (RA 9513)
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="solution-details">
      <div class="detail-box">
       <div class="detail-label">
        Current Status
       </div>
       <div class="detail-text">
        Department of Energy (DOE) actively promotes renewable energy projects. Incentivizes solar, wind, biomass, and hydro developers with guaranteed rates.
       </div>
      </div>
      <div class="detail-box">
       <div class="detail-label">
        Procedure/Program
       </div>
       <div class="detail-text">
        Provides incentives for clean energy adoption and development of renewable energy infrastructure.
       </div>
      </div>
      <div class="detail-box">
       <div class="detail-label">
        Effect/Result
       </div>
       <div class="detail-text">
        Reduces reliance on fossil fuels and lowers carbon emissions across the energy sector.
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
   </div>
